-- JFK Airport Defendants Are Found Guilty of Plotting to Blow Up Fuel Lines
-- Tiffany Kary
-- 2010-08-02T18:24:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/jfk-airport-defendants-are-found-guilty-of-plotting-to-blow-up-fuel-lines.html

          
          
             An ex-airline employee and a former
member of Guyana’s parliament were found guilty of plotting to
blow up fuel lines and tanks at New York’s John F. Kennedy
International Airport.  
 Russell Defreitas, a former Evergreen Airlines cargo
worker, and Abdul Kadir were convicted today by a jury in
federal court in Brooklyn, New York.  
